All existing tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

## Root Cause

In `MultiLineIfElseRule.kt`, line 98 calls `node.firstChildNode.elementType` without a null check. When processing the code:

```kotlin
if ("a" == "b") {
} else if ("b" == "c") else {
}
```

The `else if ("b" == "c")` part creates a THEN node with **no children** (since there's no body between `if ("b" == "c")` and `else`). When `node.firstChildNode` returns `null`, calling `.elementType` on it throws the NPE.

## Fix

Added a null check for `node.firstChildNode` early in `beforeVisitChildNodes()` at `MultiLineIfElseRule.kt:63`. If a THEN or ELSE node has no children, the method returns early — there's nothing to lint or wrap in braces.

**Change in** `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/MultiLineIfElseRule.kt:62-65`:

```kotlin
// Ignore empty THEN or ELSE blocks (e.g. `if (...) else ...`)
if (node.firstChildNode == null) {
    return
}
```

This guard prevents the NPE at both line 98 (`node.firstChildNode.elementType == IF`) and line 113 (`node.firstChildNode.startOffset`).
